---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import QuoteBlock from '../../../components/content/QuoteBlock.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Desde Adentro';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/desde-adentro/desde-adentro-01.jpg')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Desde Adentro — Work"
  description="Desde Adentro (2003). 12 C-type photographs, 12-hour video installation. Documentation of the Club El Nogal attack. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 004</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2003 &nbsp;/&nbsp; 12 C-type photographs, 12-hour video installation &nbsp;/&nbsp; 89 x 123 cm (photographs), edition of 5</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <img src={img1.src} alt="Desde Adentro — Photographic documentation of the interior of Club El Nogal after the attack" loading="eager">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Desde Adentro — Traces and marks on ash-covered surfaces ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Desde Adentro — Detail of everyday objects after the explosion ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            Five days after the terrorist attack on Club El Nogal in February 2003,
            Escallon — who served as the club's Cultural Director — documented the
            aftermath in 12 photographs and a 12-hour video. The traces of absent people
            and missing objects transport the viewer to lived moments, despite arriving
            'late to the scene of facts.'
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The photographs capture impressions found on surfaces and everyday objects
            — doors, walls, stairs — preserving the atmosphere of destruction and the
            memory of the incident. The film of ash that covered everything became a
            register of absence. The traces function as indexes of what is no longer
            there: handprints, the outlines of removed paintings, the silhouettes of
            volatilized objects.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The 12-hour video installation slowly traverses the devastated spaces,
            constructing a time parallel to that of the destruction. The camera lingers
            on details that the everyday gaze would overlook, turning the document into
            a meditation on the fragility of the spaces we inhabit.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            On February 7, 2003, a car bomb exploded inside Club El Nogal in northern
            Bogota, killing 36 people and injuring more than 200. The attack was attributed
            to the FARC and deeply shook Colombian society. Escallon's documentation became
            one of the most significant artistic responses to urban violence in Colombian
            contemporary art.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            Escallon's singular position — as both the club's Cultural Director and a visual
            artist — gave her unique access to the scene of the attack. Her documentation
            operates at the intersection between forensic record and artistic gaze,
            transforming the evidence of destruction into a reflection on loss, memory,
            and the trace as a form of presence.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            <em>Desde Adentro</em> consolidated Escallon's practice around the arrival
            'late to the scene of facts' — a position that would recur in later works
            such as <em>En estado de coma</em> — where the artist does not document the
            event itself but its consequences, the traces that remain when everything
            else has disappeared.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Desde Adentro</strong><br>
            2003<br><br>
            12 C-type photographs.<br>
            12-hour video installation.<br><br>
            89 x 123 cm (photographs)<br>
            Edition of 5<br><br>
            Club El Nogal, Bogota.
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">COLLECTIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Art Gallery of New South Wales, Sydney<br>
            Banco de la Republica, Bogota
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Art Gallery of New South Wales, Sydney<br>
            Banco de la Republica, Bogota
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">TEXTS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <a href="/es/textos/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              Related texts (ES)
            </a>
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2003). <em>Desde Adentro</em>.
            Photography and video installation. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/desde-adentro/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  .work-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--s5) + 40px);
  }

  .work-page__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__header h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin: var(--s1) 0;
  }

  .work-page__meta {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ash);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .work-page__gallery {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s2);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__gallery img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .work-page__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--s5);
    margin-bottom: var(--s5);
  }

  .work-page__text h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ash);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .work-page__ficha h4 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--ash);
    margin-bottom: var(--s1);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .placeholder-img {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: var(--paper-dark);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--ash-light);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .work-page__body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
